title: Newcastle surfer knocked out in alleged one-punch attack - 9news.com.au
text:
Newcastle surfer knocked out in alleged one-punch attack By 9NEWS Jake Sylvester, 23, has suffered serious head injuries after an alleged one-punch attack. (9NEWS) 
A competitive surfer has serious head injuries after an alleged one-punch attack at a Newcastle bar last night. 
Jake Sylvester, 23, was kicked out of a hotel on Steel Street about 11.25pm when a fight broke out on the footpath, police said. 
Witnesses told authorities Mr Sylvester was punched in the head and knocked to the ground. 
He was taken to John Hunter Hospital with a fractured skull and is being assessed for a suspected brain injury. 
Police investigations are ongoing. 
Mr Sylvester had been competing in the annual Surfest competition in Newcastle over the past week. 
Anyone with information is urged to contact Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000.
